{{Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Magic| name=Quietus| type=[[Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Magic#Spells|Spell]] (Charm)| features=Reverses effects of Sonorus| appearance=[[Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Books/Goblet of Fire/Chapter 8|Harry Potter and the Goblet of Fire]]}}
== Overview ==
The '''''Quietus''''' charm is cast by a wizard, usually upon himself, to restore his voice to its normal volume after the use of the [[Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Magic/Sonorus|Sonorus]] charm.
== Extended Description ==
{{Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Beginner Spoiler}}
The Quietus charm is first seen used by [[Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Characters/Ludovic Bagman|Ludo Bagman]] when he is called upon to commentate the [[Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Major Events/Quidditch World Cup|Quidditch World Cup]]; when the game is finished, Ludo ends his earlier Sonorus charm by invoking Quietus.
Ludo uses this spell again after commentating the events in the [[Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Major Events/Triwizard Tournament|Triwizard Tournament]].
