Templates used in the [[Cookbook]].
[[Category:Cookbook utility categories]] [[Category:Namespace-specific templates]]

{{equipment}} | [[Cookbook:Utensil|Utensils]] [[Image:Old carving knife and forks.JPG|right|thumb|Carving knife and forks]]
'''Carving knife''' is the term for blades that resemble a [[Cookbook:Chef's Knife|chef's knife]], but may be longer and more slender. It is useful for cutting large samples of poultry and other meats, often used in conjunction with a [[Cookbook:Fork|fork]]. It is important that any knives are kept sharp, as blunt knives require more force to use, actually increasing the likelihood of injury (cuts from a sharp knife heal more quickly than those from a blunt one). A [[Cookbook:Knife Sharpener|knife sharpener]] can be used to keep knives sharp.
{{Wikipedia|Kitchen knife}}

